258
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:43,531
We're practicing diving.

259
00:13:43,698 --> 00:13:46,200
Why won't you tell me the truth?

260
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:48,286
I did tell you the truth!

261
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:52,040
You're engaged in some sort of advanced adult activity!

262
00:13:52,457 --> 00:13:54,751
No, this is for beginners.

263
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:58,755
Aina, we really are practicing diving.

264
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:02,759
-Really?
-Why do you believe it when Chisa says it?

265
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:06,262
We were practicing mask clearing.

266
00:14:06,471 --> 00:14:08,139
I see.

267
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:10,725
Then you should have told me earlier.

268
00:14:10,892 --> 00:14:13,186
I didn't want you to laugh at me.

269
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:16,731
I wouldn't laugh at you!
I would've helped you if you had told me.

270
00:14:16,898 --> 00:14:19,025
-Really?
-That'd be a big help.

271
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:20,860
So, what should I do?

272
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:22,528
Oh, well, then...

273
00:14:30,787 --> 00:14:33,539
-Don't struggle!
-Stop kicking!

274
00:14:33,706 --> 00:14:35,041
Hello. Is this the police?

275
00:14:37,168 --> 00:14:39,420
There's still water in my mask.

276
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:42,006
You're almost there.

277
00:14:42,173 --> 00:14:44,342
Maybe you're still afraid of the water.

278
00:14:44,509 --> 00:14:46,427
It's come down to this. Let's do it.

279
00:14:46,677 --> 00:14:48,429
It?

280
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:51,516
Yeah. We did it before.

281
00:14:52,809 --> 00:14:54,811
I'm in a bathtub.

282
00:14:54,977 --> 00:14:56,270
I'm in a bathtub.

283
00:14:56,437 --> 00:14:59,315
-You did this before?
-I had nothing to do with it.

284
00:14:59,482 --> 00:15:01,776
Does that really work?

285
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:04,403
-No. It didn't work at all.
-What?

286
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,197
Then why are you doing it?

287
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,286
I thought...

288
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:15,540
I'd be able to get closer here.

289
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:19,919
I want to do everything I can.

290
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:23,881
Anyway, you can go to sleep.

291
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:26,926
-Okay.
-Don't overdo it.

292
00:15:27,093 --> 00:15:28,970
Thanks for coming.

293
00:15:29,137 --> 00:15:30,847
-Goodnight.
-Goodnight.

294
00:15:31,013 --> 00:15:32,932
Yeah, good night.

295
00:15:34,684 --> 00:15:35,977
Well, then...

296
00:15:45,319 --> 00:15:47,738
All right. Not bad.

297
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:49,407
Excuse me.

298
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,493
I'm from the police.

299
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:57,290
Someone reported a girl and a guy
engaging in unusual behavior.

300
00:15:57,456 --> 00:16:00,376
Well... I think there's been a mistake.

301
00:16:00,543 --> 00:16:04,005
I didn't see anyone suspicious.

302
00:16:04,213 --> 00:16:05,756
-Oh, really?
-Yes.

303
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:09,510
I didn't see any dangerous people like that.

304
00:16:10,094 --> 00:16:14,515
Just in case, I'm going to look around
to make sure there's no one suspicious here.

305
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:17,018
I understand.

306
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,274
I can't get out.

307
00:16:33,492 --> 00:16:36,287
You're saying Iori's in bed because he caught a cold?

308
00:16:36,495 --> 00:16:37,622
That's right.

309
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:40,208
When I woke up, his face was red.

310
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:41,542
I was surprised.

311
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:47,423
-Iori's always like that!
-Even the way idiots get sick is different.

312
00:16:47,632 --> 00:16:51,135
His fever isn't that high, so I think he'll be okay.

313
00:16:51,302 --> 00:16:53,429
He can't participate in today's lessons.

314
00:16:53,596 --> 00:16:55,932
It's because of what I said.

315
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:59,435
No, it's not your fault.

316
00:16:59,602 --> 00:17:02,939
This is obviously his own fault.

317
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:04,899
Anyway...

318
00:17:05,066 --> 00:17:07,026
Let's let Iori sleep.

319
00:17:07,193 --> 00:17:10,821
Aina and Kohei have to concentrate
on getting their licenses.

320
00:17:10,988 --> 00:17:12,949
-Yes!
-Okay.

321
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:24,460
I feel better after sleeping.

322
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:30,216
Oh, you look like you're feeling better, Iori.

323
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:33,261
Azusa, you didn't go diving?

324
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:36,055
-Yeah.
-Sorry. It's my fault.

325
00:17:36,222 --> 00:17:37,848
What are you talking about?

326
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:39,976
So, how are you feeling?

327
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:41,852
I'm feeling much better.

328
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:44,480
It'd be best if you took some medicine,

329
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:46,524
but the pharmacy isn't open.

330
00:17:46,691 --> 00:17:48,067
There's no need for that.

331
00:17:48,234 --> 00:17:49,610
No, Iori!

332
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:52,280
You're going in the ocean tomorrow.

333
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:53,990
So, you have to fully recover.

334
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:56,659
They didn't have any medicine,

335
00:17:56,826 --> 00:17:58,577
but they had this.

336
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:06,335
Azusa, what's that?

337
00:18:06,502 --> 00:18:08,629
A famous home remedy. You don't know it?

338
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:10,715
I know. I do know.

339
00:18:10,881 --> 00:18:12,258
The only problem is...

340
00:18:12,425 --> 00:18:13,592
Is it number 1 or 2?

341
00:18:14,135 --> 00:18:15,845
All right, Iori.

342
00:18:16,846 --> 00:18:17,888
Yes?

343
00:18:18,055 --> 00:18:20,057
Stick out your neck.

344
00:18:21,058 --> 00:18:22,935
Good, it's number 1!

345
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:26,105
-What's wrong?
-Nothing.

346
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:31,610
-Here. Okay.
-Thank you.

347
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:33,654
ANOTHER ONE

348
00:18:33,821 --> 00:18:35,906
Can you pull down your pants next?

349
00:18:36,073 --> 00:18:38,159
No, a combination technique!

350
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:41,120
Azusa, you don't have to do this for me!

351
00:18:41,287 --> 00:18:43,414
No, no. There's no medicine.

352
00:18:43,581 --> 00:18:44,915
So we have to do this.

353
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,918
No. If I don't do something,

354
00:18:48,419 --> 00:18:51,422
something else other than my health
is going to be destroyed!

355
00:18:53,299 --> 00:18:55,926
I'm going to look for some other medicine!

356
00:18:58,137 --> 00:19:01,140
This is perfect for medicine, right?

357
00:19:01,307 --> 00:19:04,518
True. It disinfects, stimulates perspiration,
and induces sleep.

358
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:06,437
It's also rich in nutrients.

359
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:09,940
It's the best medicine!

360
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:12,943
Sick people shouldn't drink it though.

361
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:16,947
But, if I drink now and fall sleep,
I won't be able to sleep at night.

362
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:19,950
You haven't been able to sleep at night anyway.

363
00:19:20,117 --> 00:19:22,411
That's for a different reason.

364
00:19:22,578 --> 00:19:23,829
A different reason?

365
00:19:23,996 --> 00:19:25,373
You know...

366
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:28,125
I feel nervous sleeping next to you and Nanaka,

367
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:30,586
so I can't fall asleep.

368
00:19:30,753 --> 00:19:32,630
Oh, I didn't know that.

369
00:19:32,797 --> 00:19:35,800
Sorry about that.

370
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:38,344
Azusa?

371
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:40,805
-Hey, Iori.
-Yes?

372
00:19:41,931 --> 00:19:43,307
Do you want to have sex?

373
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:50,731
-What are you saying!?
-You won't be nervous anymore, right?

374
00:19:50,898 --> 00:19:53,692
No! It's not something to do so casually!

375
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:55,569
That's so rude.

376
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:58,739
I don't do it with just any guy.

377
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:03,369
But I do like you.

378
00:20:03,619 --> 00:20:05,287
I'm fine with doing it once.

379
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:07,498
She's acting like it's a sport!

380
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:10,000
I'm half joking.

381
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:12,545
It'd be bad if things got awkward between us.

382
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:14,255
Half?

383
00:20:14,797 --> 00:20:17,758
Yeah. Half.

384
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:22,263
If you seriously want to do it, I'm okay with that.

385
00:20:27,518 --> 00:20:28,769
I'm being tested!

386
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:30,521
I'm...

387
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:32,273
really...

388
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:34,275
being tested right now!

389
00:20:36,819 --> 00:20:38,279
I'm...

390
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:40,322
going to say no.

391
00:20:41,741 --> 00:20:43,284
That's too bad.

392
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:47,746
By the way, Azusa...

393
00:20:48,706 --> 00:20:51,876
You like Tokita as well as Nanaka, right?

394
00:20:52,042 --> 00:20:53,043
That's right.

395
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:56,547
Why don't you go after Tokita?

396
00:20:58,466 --> 00:21:01,218
Tokki is kind of, you know...

397
00:21:01,385 --> 00:21:03,137
I'd be wasting my time chasing him.

398
00:21:03,304 --> 00:21:05,556
So it's different with Nanaka?

399
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:07,641
A waste of time? Why?

400
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:09,935
Don't you know, Iori?

401
00:21:10,102 --> 00:21:13,314
-What?
-Tokki, you know...

402
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:15,983
has a girlfriend.

403
00:21:20,154 --> 00:21:22,490
-He has a girlfriend?
-Yeah. A girlfriend.

404
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:24,909
-A homosexual?
-Why would she be homosexual?

405
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:26,702
Homo sapiens?

406
00:21:26,869 --> 00:21:29,955
So you were asking about her species?
She is a human.

407
00:21:30,206 --> 00:21:33,000
I see. Tokita has a girlfriend!

408
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:35,586
That's right!

409
00:21:36,212 --> 00:21:39,215
-Let's drink.
-What's wrong all of a sudden?

410
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:42,343
Darn! Why does he have a girlfriend but not me?

411
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:44,762
Wow, you're drinking a lot!

412
00:21:53,729 --> 00:21:55,648
Congratulations on getting your license.

413
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:58,108
You're real divers now.

414
00:21:58,275 --> 00:22:01,695
-Congratulations.
-I'm not sure about her though.

415
00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:05,491
-I'm going to get better!
-That's the right attitude!

416
00:22:05,658 --> 00:22:08,244
All right! We're going to Miyakojima tomorrow!

417
00:22:10,704 --> 00:22:14,083
Let's have a toast first!

418
00:22:20,214 --> 00:22:22,299
It looks like they already did.

419
00:22:22,466 --> 00:22:24,635
He's all better. Good.

420
00:22:24,802 --> 00:22:27,137
Oh, dear. They're so impatient!

421
00:22:30,641 --> 00:22:31,642
A masochist...

422
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:36,021
DEEP BLUE AL FINE
KAYA MIZUKI

423
00:22:44,905 --> 00:22:50,911
A fairytale whispers
In a fake world

424
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:56,834
Hiding in the complete darkness

425
00:22:57,001 --> 00:23:02,798
I reach for the forbidden fruit
In my last days

426
00:23:02,965 --> 00:23:09,054
Now I know the meaning of the song about hope

427
00:23:09,263 --> 00:23:14,351
A broken gear will never stop again

428
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:22,067
Even if I were to lose everything
I'd still want you to know

429
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:28,282
Trapped in the sky so far away
I'm praying with ripped off wings

430
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:34,121
Because we span together
The vows of arpeggio

431
00:23:34,288 --> 00:23:40,044
If life sparkles only to the beat
Of the resonating stars

432
00:23:40,210 --> 00:23:43,047
I'll sacrifice everything

433
00:23:43,213 --> 00:23:48,302
Till death do us apart

434
00:23:54,558 --> 00:23:57,102
Thanks, everybody!

435
00:24:02,483 --> 00:24:03,651
Yeah!

436
00:24:10,449 --> 00:24:13,410
Hey, don't act so crazy, freshman.

437
00:24:13,619 --> 00:24:15,788
All right. Let's begin.

438
00:24:15,813 --> 00:24:16,955
NEXT EPISODE
"OTORI"
